    {
      "id": "x7RfY_8QEFz4OYA0Yjr6b",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 476.1454245827415,
      "y": 173.65739137476123,
      "width": 822.039306640625,
      "height": 625,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ad",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 584829464,
      "version": 1229,
      "versionNonce": 1591374104,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775932793214,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Requirements\n\nFunctional (Core Features):\n1.  User should be able to start Group chat.\n2. Send / Receive Messages. -> Media Attachments like images / video / documents.\n3. Access the messages in case of offline.\n\n-- out of scope ---\n1. Audio /video calling\n2. Seeing status of people in a group chat -> If they are online or offline.\n3. Able to edit / delete messages.\n\n\n\nNon Functional ( Perforamance & Optimizations ):\n1. Delivered messages with low latency ->  < 500 ms should be fine.\n2. Guarentee delivery of messages  [ consistency should be guarntee ]\n3. scalebility scope -> Billions of users, high throughput.\n4. Messages not stored unnecesarly.\n5. Fault - tolerant especially for a system like whatsapp.\n\n-- out of scope ---\n1. Authentication of messages.\n2. Protection and sanitization of message contexts.\n3. User GDPR.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Requirements\n\nFunctional (Core Features):\n1.  User should be able to start Group chat.\n2. Send / Receive Messages. -> Media Attachments like images / video / documents.\n3. Access the messages in case of offline.\n\n-- out of scope ---\n1. Audio /video calling\n2. Seeing status of people in a group chat -> If they are online or offline.\n3. Able to edit / delete messages.\n\n\n\nNon Functional ( Perforamance & Optimizations ):\n1. Delivered messages with low latency ->  < 500 ms should be fine.\n2. Guarentee delivery of messages  [ consistency should be guarntee ]\n3. scalebility scope -> Billions of users, high throughput.\n4. Messages not stored unnecesarly.\n5. Fault - tolerant especially for a system like whatsapp.\n\n-- out of scope ---\n1. Authentication of messages.\n2. Protection and sanitization of message contexts.\n3. User GDPR.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "VksGx-tQvGWIVWBkX5Z7O",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1594.9888257726864,
      "y": 145.60592057158385,
      "width": 595.8995971679688,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "af",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 978394136,
      "version": 333,
      "versionNonce": 2125762408,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776096133666,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Core Entities\n1. User - all users of the system\n2. chat\n3. Messages\n4. Client / Devices  - Where the application is accessed from.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Entities\n1. User - all users of the system\n2. chat\n3. Messages\n4. Client / Devices  - Where the application is accessed from.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "aNdYTR4hKoUJRJUIJxOGh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1593.2087952434265,
      "y": 341.24737992616235,
      "width": 1108.079345703125,
      "height": 600,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ah",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 838751768,
      "version": 1122,
      "versionNonce": 400383000,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776096136733,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "API \n\nNow Appliction like Whatsapp, it doesnot make any sence of having a Restful API where\nwe need a constant open connection or medium of messaging between client and server.\n\nAs per the rule lets see....\n    - Is whatsapp latency sensitive ?? --> well yes ! we need message to deliver faster.\n    - Is whatsapp Frequent bi-directional communication ?  --> messages will be coming in and out quiet frequently.\n    - Does it needs a peer to peer Real time connection ? -> WEll not exactly.\n        \nConclusion: \"websockets\" should make sense here.\n\n\nCommands Send:\n    -  createChat\n    -  sendMessages  \n    - createAttachment\n    - modifyParticipants\n\n\nCommands Received:\n    - newMessage\n    - chatUpdate - whenever new chats are created or participants are updated.\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "API \n\nNow Appliction like Whatsapp, it doesnot make any sence of having a Restful API where\nwe need a constant open connection or medium of messaging between client and server.\n\nAs per the rule lets see....\n    - Is whatsapp latency sensitive ?? --> well yes ! we need message to deliver faster.\n    - Is whatsapp Frequent bi-directional communication ?  --> messages will be coming in and out quiet frequently.\n    - Does it needs a peer to peer Real time connection ? -> WEll not exactly.\n        \nConclusion: \"websockets\" should make sense here.\n\n\nCommands Send:\n    -  createChat\n    -  sendMessages  \n    - createAttachment\n    - modifyParticipants\n\n\nCommands Received:\n    - newMessage\n    - chatUpdate - whenever new chats are created or participants are updated.\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ZRYesUaCgCz2w6A7MkFVK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3030.445402605759,
