    {
      "id": "oZsOn_LMwt_PD7XDcbfNV",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1628.4458581395284,
      "y": 1291.0728270004192,
      "width": 1269.5791015625,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0X",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1556973416,
      "version": 1431,
      "versionNonce": 758970648,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776096264583,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How do we make sure Offline delivery/access of Messages\n    - 2 new entites we need:\n        1. messages -> keep track of the content of a message.\n        2. Index -> it's like a queue that tracks the message deliverables\n    \n    Flow:\n       - So the client send a message to a chat with some Id to chat-service.\n       - Chat-service will look into chatParticipants to find list or participants for that chatId.\n       - The message will be with the message enity -> and an entry is added to Indox.\n       - 2 cases:\n           1. Recipient is offline.\n                - If the guy is offline, messages keeps queing up in Inbox.\n                - The moment my guy connects -> Chat service -> Offloads all messages corresponding to his recipientId from Inbox.\n                - Once Deliveries and client service receive confirmation from client -> clear recrods from Inbox\n\n           2. Recipient is online:\n               - In this case, client service checks the corresponding WS connection and sends the message back.\n               - Once the message is received -> we remove the entry from the Inbox -> Guarenties Delivery. \n\n    This gurantees messages are eventually delivered to the client. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How do we make sure Offline delivery/access of Messages\n    - 2 new entites we need:\n        1. messages -> keep track of the content of a message.\n        2. Index -> it's like a queue that tracks the message deliverables\n    \n    Flow:\n       - So the client send a message to a chat with some Id to chat-service.\n       - Chat-service will look into chatParticipants to find list or participants for that chatId.\n       - The message will be with the message enity -> and an entry is added to Indox.\n       - 2 cases:\n           1. Recipient is offline.\n                - If the guy is offline, messages keeps queing up in Inbox.\n                - The moment my guy connects -> Chat service -> Offloads all messages corresponding to his recipientId from Inbox.\n                - Once Deliveries and client service receive confirmation from client -> clear recrods from Inbox\n\n           2. Recipient is online:\n               - In this case, client service checks the corresponding WS connection and sends the message back.\n               - Once the message is received -> we remove the entry from the Inbox -> Guarenties Delivery. \n\n    This gurantees messages are eventually delivered to the client. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
